title: Andricus quercuscalicis 20190517131036
description: The sexual generation gall of Andricus quercuscalicis is a very small gall found on the male catkins of Quercus cerris. The asexual (agamic) gall is the well known "Knopper Gall". This forms on the acorns of Quercus robur and Quercus petraea. This photograph shows females of the sexual generation laying eggs into the female flowers of Quercus robur. These will produce the agamic generation gall - the knopper gall.
label: Original
